[[Vice Admiral]] '''Charles Morris Winton ('Chuck') Thomas''' [[Order of Military Merit (Canada)|CMM]] (born 31 May 1936) is a retired [[Canadian Forces]] officer who served as [[Vice Chief of the Defence Staff (Canada)|Vice Chief of the Defence Staff]].

==Career==
Thomas joined the [[Royal Canadian Navy]] in 1954.<ref name=naut>[http://nauticapedia.ca/dbase/Query/Biolist3.php?name=Thomas,%20Charles%20Morris%20Winton&id=21387&Page=1&input=Thomas,%20Charles%20Morris%20Winton Charles Thomas] The Nauticapedia</ref> He became Commanding Officer of the [[destroyer]] {{HMCS|Fraser|DDH 233|6}} in 1971, Senior Staff Officer (Training) in 1973 and Senior Staff Officer (Combat Readiness) in 1973.<ref name=naut/> He went on to be Chief of Staff (Personnel & Training) in 1975, Commanding Officer of the 4th Canadian Escort Squadron in 1976 and Director Maritime Requirements (Sea)  at the [[National Defence Headquarters (Canada)|National Defence Headquarters]] in 1979.<ref name=naut/> After that he was Director General Maritime Doctrine and Operations in 1982, Chief of Maritime Doctrine and Operations in 1984 and [[Commander of the Royal Canadian Navy|Commander Maritime Command]] in 1987.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=DTXDGrVfRFYC&pg=PA8&lpg=PA8&dq=Admiral+Robert+George+canada&source=bl&ots=S0HJ8SD_kJ&sig=H-tvIzrb8Pz9cXC4p_lZp-uKv78&hl=en&sa=X&ei=cYE1Uo3KC4SThQey24GADA&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAjgK#v=onepage&q=Admiral%20Robert%20George%20canada&f=false The Admirals: Canada's Senior Naval Leadership in the Twentieth Century] edited by Michel Whitby, Toronto: Dundurn Press, 2006, p. 335</ref> His last appointment was as [[Vice Chief of the Defence Staff (Canada)|Vice Chief of the Defence Staff]] in 1989 before resigning over policy issues in 1991.<ref name=naut/> His resignation reflected his belief that the Canadian Government should have been reducing the network of 40 armed forces bases rather than just reducing the headcount.<ref>[http://business.highbeam.com/4341/article-1G1-10715650/admiral-call-close-more-bases The admiral's call: close more bases]  Maclean's, May 13, 1991</ref> General [[John de Chastelain]], Chief of the Defence Staff, responded attacking Thomas' motives rather than responding to his concerns.<ref>[http://www.thefreelibrary.com/A+new+era+begins.-a0198412475 A new era begins] Esprit de Corps, 1 April 2009</ref>

